 library  At the request of VMI cadets and faculty  Interlibrary Loan staff borrow research materials not owned by Preston Library from other libraries in Virginia and the United States  Government Publications  650 level    Preston Library maintains a selective federal depository of government publications   Designated in 1874  the depository collection includes materials from the departments of Commerce  Defense  Interior  Labor  State  and others   Questions regarding government information are handled by the depository librarian during reference hours  Media Services  4th floor    The Media Services Department provides services dealing with audio visual materials  including reserving AV materials for rental or purchase  loaning AV equipment for classroom use  videotaping  editing  photography  duplication of video and audio tapes for academic use  dry mounting and laminating  and reference guidance for AV software and equipment rentals and purchases  Service requests must be made with as much advance notice as possible  Reference  5th floor    The Reference Department coordinates library instruction  works with library patrons conducting research  and is available to answer more detailed research and general interest questions  Members of this department work with instructors to coordinate the use of library resources and with students on research projects  Technical Services  4th floor    The Technical Services Department manages the acquisition and cataloging of library materials  VMI Archives 4th floor    The Archives manages the Institute s historic official records  manuscripts  photographs  and 19th century alumni biographical and genealogical information  Rare books and other rare materials are located in the VMI Archives  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 